The article is a statement by the White House Press Secretary on Ukrainian Holodomor Remembrance Day. It acknowledges the suffering endured by the people of Ukraine during the Holodomor, a famine caused by Joseph Stalin's intentional seizure of crops and farms. The statement emphasizes the courage and resilience of the Ukrainian people in the aftermath of this tragedy and celebrates Ukraine's independence. The United States expresses its condolences and reaffirms its commitment to preventing similar acts from happening again.